RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 15000. (PLUS UP TO $3,000 Open ATB) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $15,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MISS DISTINCTIVE broke well, allowed to settle into stride off the pace, launched a sustained rally from the three-eighths pole splitting horses to take command in the lane and draw off under constant urging. CRIMSON LADY dueled for the early lead down the backstretch, opened a clear advantage on the turn and could not hold off the winner. POET LAUREATE away at the rear of the field, trailed to the top of the lane and launched a belated five wide rally in the lane to gain the show. CHEER UP raced up the rail to battle for the lead and gave way through the stretch. MRSG'S LIL DREAMER tracked the leaders through midway on the turn and tired through the lane while drifting out.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 9 7 1/2F Turf CR: 92. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 34500. (PLUS UP TO $6,900 Open ATB) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TEXAS BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $30,000. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since January 16, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since October 16, 2022 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $30,000 (Maiden Or Claiming Races Not Considered In Allowances). (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run thi s race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile. If the race is for two year olds, it will be run at Seven Furlongs.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COLORS OF THE WIND was in tight heading into the first turn, then saved ground down the backstretch, was gaining from the four path on the far turn to dig in gamely in the early stretch, then vied with inner rivals in late stretch and was up just in time to prove best. SHE'SSKYSTHELIMIT stalked the pace from the three path down the backstretch, was under a strong drive throughout the second turn, angled in towards the rail to menace in the early stretch, then vied for win in deep stretch but hung in the end and was second best. TUDELA was two wide heading into the first turn, then gained command in the early backstretch, cleared the second turn, rallied in the upper stretch, then vied to keep the lead in deep stretch but was out finished in the end and was best for the show prize. MISSION BELLE chased the pace from the three path, then bid while four wide on the far turn to rally gamely in the upper stretch, vied for the lead between rivals in the final furlong but hung in the end. PRINCESS PAULINE chased the pace in the middle of the field from the inside, then bid mildly on the far turn to close well in the stretch. QUINN ELLA lead the way into the first turn, then was over taken for the lead down the early backstretch, was under a steady hand ride throughout the far turn to rally mid stretch but came up empty in the end. LEARNING TO WIN was unhurried early, then settled while two wide down the backstretch, was moving up throughout the second turn to bid from the sixth path down the home stretch but it was too little too late. DISCREET SMILE chased the pace while two wide down the backstretch, then steadied on the far turn and lost momentum in the stretch. FEELING HAPPY was shuffled back shortly after the start, was unhurried early, then settled along the rail down the backstretch, bid while four wide on the turn and into the stretch and was no threat. MY BABYS GONE chased the pace while four wide down the backstretch, then bid on the far turn to rally in the stretch but did not fire.
